{{Infobox magazine | name = Biser | logo = Biser first issue.jpg | image = | caption = | type = | format = | founder = [[Muhamed Bekir Kalajdžić]] | publisher = | president = | editor = [[Musa Ćazim Ćatić]] | staff = | frequency = | founded = 1 June 1912 | political = | language = [[Bosnian language|Bosnian]] | finaldate = 1919 | headquarters = | based = [[Mostar]] | country = [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] | issn = | oclc = | website = }} '''''Biser''''' was a [[Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnian]] magazine, intended as a non-political replacement for the defunct ''[[Behar (magazine)|Behar]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EB5pAAAAMAAJ&q=Muhamed+Bekir+Kalajd%C5%BEi%C4%87&dq=Muhamed+Bekir+Kalajd%C5%BEi%C4%87|title=Anali Gazi Husrev-begove bibliotheke|publisher=|year=2001|accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref> The first issue was published 1 June 1912 out of [[Mostar]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] by 19-year-old publisher [[Muhamed Bekir Kalajdžić]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bosnjaci.net/prilog.php?pid=41321|title=BISER, NA PRAGU STOTE GODIŠNJICE|publisher=Bosnjaci|date=5 April 2011|accessdate=7 April 2016}}</ref> The main objective of ''Biser'' was to focus on [[Bosniak]] culture and heritage, as well as Muslim literary works. The Bosnian word ''biser'' means pearl in English.
Poet [[Musa Ćazim Ćatić]] served as editor in chief, often writing poems, essays, criticism, and translations of numerous studies and books for the magazine.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iGQMAQAAMAAJ&q=Muhamed+Bekir+Kalajd%C5%BEi%C4%87&dq=Muhamed+Bekir+Kalajd%C5%BEi%C4%87&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjw146i1P3LAhXFOSYKHQIXCc4Q6AEIRDAG|title=Hercegovina, Volumes 15-16|publisher=|year=2003|accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=t7JiAAAAMAAJ&q=Muhamed+Bekir+Kalajd%C5%BEi%C4%87&dq=Muhamed+Bekir+Kalajd%C5%BEi%C4%87&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi05Zje3P3LAhWB4CYKHdUjAtM4ChDoAQhaMAk|title=Biserje: antologija muslimanske književnosti|publisher=|year=1990|accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XXNBAAAAIAAJ&q=Muhamed+Bekir+Kalajd%C5%BEi%C4%87&dq=Muhamed+Bekir+Kalajd%C5%BEi%C4%87&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjhp9Tk6P3LAhUIYyYKHbfaCqY4FBDoAQgiMAE|title=Musa Ćazim Ćatić: Studija|publisher=|year=1965|accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref>
Due to the outbreak of [[World War I]] in 1914, ''Biser'' halted production until 1918 when Kalajdžić began printing again in 1918 to avoid being drafted into the army. ''Biser'' ended its run in 1919.
