The '''Bloody Carnival''' ({{lang-hu|véres farsang}}) was the massacre of [[Székelys|Székely]] serfs in February 1596 after their rebellion for the restoration of their freedom.{{sfn|Barta|1994|p=295}} The Székelys rose up because the [[Diet of Transylvania]] had refused to restore their freedom.{{sfn|Barta|1994|p=295}}{{sfn|G. Etényi|Horn|Szabó|2006|p=128}} [[Sigismund Báthory]], [[Prince of Transylvania]] promised them to restore their freedom if they joined his campaign against the [[Ottoman Empire|Ottomans]] in [[Wallachia]] in autumn 1595.{{sfn|Barta|1994|p=295}}{{sfn|G. Etényi|Horn|Szabó|2006|p=128}}

